*[[Strong's concordance]] number:  [http://www.biblestudytools.net/Lexicons/Greek/grk.cgi?number=5259&version=kjv G5259] 

===Pronunciation===
*ὑπό / hupo / hoop-o'
=== Etymology ===

*A primary preposition; 

*In compounds it retains the same genitive applications, especially of inferior position or condition, and specifically covertly or moderately.
=== Preposition ===
[[under]], that is, (with the genitive) of place (beneath), or with verbs (the agency or means, through); (with the accusative) of place (whither [underneath] or where [below]) or time (when [at]): 

- among, by, from, in, of, under, with.